HEADWORD: Puerperal
<hw>Pu*er"per*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>puerpera</ets> a lying-in woman; <ets>puer</ets> child +
<ets>parere</ets> to bear: cf. F. <ets>puerp⟦eacute⟧ral</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Of or pertaining to childbirth; <as>as, a <ex>puerperal</ex>
fever</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
